            <p n="0001">
                <s n="0001.001">Suddenly the catbird uttered a piercing scream and disappeared from
                    the cross on the chapel.</s>
                <s n="0001.002"> And <persName ref="#philip_montel">Philip</persName> turned to see
                    entering from the leftwing of the stage under a green pine tree a white clothed
                    woman--a <seg ana="#con-mech">doll-like</seg>
                    <seg ana="#trans-inf">Lorelei</seg>.</s>
                <s n="0001.003">Two translucent silver eagle wings hovered--shimmering--above the
                    tree, their <seg ana="#rep-ang">silvery light casting a sheen upon
                    her</seg>.</s>
                <s n="0001.004">She too moved on the tips of her toes.</s>
                <s n="0001.005">But more as if she were a <seg ana="#con-mech">toy</seg>, or a <seg
                        ana="#con-mech">goddess on wheels</seg>.</s>
                <s n="0001.006" ana="#con-lit">She did not look to right or to left.</s>
                <s n="0001.007">She held in her small white hands a piece of <seg ana="#con-dom"
                        >sheer linen upon which she was embroidering</seg> a <seg ana="trans-inf"
                        >red strawberry</seg>.</s>
                <s n="0001.008">Her golden hair was drawn into a psyche knot at the nape of her neck
                    and a small jade bird on a thin gold <seg ana="#con-lit">chain was fastened at
                        her throat</seg>.</s>
                <s n="0001.009">She looked like a <seg ana="rep-ang">porcelain</seg>
                    <seg ana="con-mech">automaton</seg>——<seg ana="rep-ang">daintily painted pink
                        and white</seg>——<seg ana="con-mech">with some workings inside</seg> that
                    caused her to embroider.</s>
                <s n="0001.010">From under her <seg ana="con-clo">skirt</seg>, tiny black ballet
                    shoes peeked as she moved gently forward--as if <seg ana="con-mech">wound by a
                        key</seg>.</s>
                <s n="0001.011">As she came to the water she continued to float.</s>
                <s n="0001.012">Intent upon her embroidery, she glided about, on the tips of her
                    toes, upon the glassy surface of the lake.</s>
            </p>
            <p n="0002">
                <s n="0002.001">Swaying a little in the soft breeze, her eyes upon her needle, she
                    moved as in a trance——slowly toward the opposite shore, where there was a tiny
                    pier painted red.</s>
            </p>
            <p n="0003">
                <s n="0003.001">Fastened to it was a dainty row boat. It was blue and white and
                    looked as spruce as a new toy.</s>
                <s n="0003.002">Circled about it were waterlilies, abundant and fresh--as clean and
                    white as songs.</s>
                <s n="0003.003">Along the sandy shore lay chalk stones and clusters of blue
                    iris.</s>
                <s n="0003.004">Backstage, a mandolin was picking away at an inconsequential
                    melody.</s>
            </p>

